results.title: Thoughts for Today from a Square Egg
results.description:
A few nights ago...in the middle of the night, I got up and wrote most of these thoughts.  Some have already been posted within my other lists.  If you don't have the $$ to pay for this word document, here it is below.

Here's wishing you a good day.

Sincerely, 

Esther Monsalve
The Angel Shop

Thoughts for Todayfrom a Square Egg

1.  Be aware of yourself and your surrounding ...What you say and do can have a positive or negative effect on others.

2.  Care for other's thoughts and feelings so they will care for you as well.  (a "you-me" moment).

3.  Listening and hearing - One is easier than the other...most times...selective.

4.  Being wise, smart or clever determines how well you succeed...being kind, gentle and loving determines the same...and a lot more.

5.  Always...be kind, gentle and loving to all you meet and know...

6.  Words are not always necessary when you're with someone you love and respect.

7.  Even at the age of 61 - maturity is still difficult for me to achieve.

8. Hug your child(ren) today and everyday.  Their memories of you tomorrow and years to come truly has a powerful impact during their adult lives....and their children.

9.  Misery loves misery...  Love...loves to be loved.

10.  Praying for others and preying on others = total opposites...aka...Bringing in the sheep or shearing in the sheep.

11.  Make an effort in everything you want or wish to do.  Start with baby steps...

12.  I took the leap and a net appeared (metaphor)...having strong faith in God is powerful.

13.  From now on...the only baggage I want to carry around is whenever I'm checking in at the airport.  You...do the same.

14.  In whatever shape or form...Love is the essence of life.

15.  Good teachers teach you how to learn.

16.  Lost and Found Department:
 (a.)  Peace  
 (b.)  Hope  
 (c.)  Love  
 (d.)  Kindness
 (f.)   Generosity  
 (g.)  Faith in God

17.  Taking sides or favorites is not a good idea for your family's health...unless you're dining at your favorite restaurant.

18.  Molly (good-time) = Bubba (jail-time).

19. The brain is a mindless thing to waste.

20.  The only support I have right now is my fruit-of-the-loom bra.  (they're also my support group).

©Esther Monsalve                                                                     The Angel Shop

Note: Please use MEMO, an editor writing software, in oder to open this digital file.
